pullRequest.title: Show Item's star ratings in new search page
pullRequest.bodyText:
Checklist

 the [contributor license agreement][] is signed
 commit message follows [commit guidelines][]1
 tests are included
 screenshots are included showing significant UI changes
 documentation is changed or added

Description of change
The changes included in this PR are:

Back-end change to support returning star rating from search2.
REST Module change - adding star ratings to the type definition of SearchResultItem.
Component SearchResult change - showing stars
A test for this feature.

commit.message: Include Item's star ratings in search2 response.

Update the type definition of search result Item to
include star rating.
Use MUI star icons to represent Item's ratings.
Show star ratings when the rating is 0.
Improve the accessibility of MUI Star icons.
Add a JEST test to check if Item's star ratings are displayed.

commit.message: Add a new component and Storybook for StarRating.

Move component StarRating to the right folder and update imports
of this component.
Add a Jest test for component StarRating.

nodes.bodyText:
Probably good to rename this something like 'HalfStarRating' - as that's the state I guess you're demonstrating here (that is, where one of the stars is only half).
Probably then good to also have stories to cover the examples of:

No stars;
Full stars; and
Different number of stars.

nodes.bodyText:
Either this (or additional tests) should be testing boundaries. That is:

Testing for ratings of: 0, half max, max, max + 1;
Testing for number of stars: 0, 5, lots; amd
Testing your rounding logic - to make sure it goes up to half, down to whole, etc.

Being able to easily test all that (at speed) is the real benefit you get here of splitting it out. And combined with parametrised tests, you should be able to do that succinctly.

by Star Icons.
